(Common Misconceptions) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Several widespread misconceptions complicate student) Tj T*
(understanding of photosynthesis. This section addresses three) Tj T*
(of the most common.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Misconception: Plants get their food from the soil.) Tj T*
(Correction: Plants produce their own food through) Tj T*
(photosynthesis. Soil provides water and mineral nutrients) Tj T*
(but not the carbon that makes up plant biomass; that carbon) Tj T*
(comes from atmospheric carbon dioxide.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Misconception: Plants only photosynthesize during the day.) Tj T*
(Correction: The light-dependent reactions require light, but) Tj T*
(the Calvin cycle can continue for a short time in darkness) Tj T*
(using the ATP and NADPH already produced. Plants also) Tj T*
(respire continuously, using oxygen and releasing carbon) Tj T*
(dioxide around the clock.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Misconception: Green plants absorb green light.) Tj T*
(Correction: Plants appear green because they reflect green) Tj T*
(light. Chlorophyll absorbs most strongly in the red and) Tj T*
(blue ranges and poorly in green, which is why the reflected) Tj T*
(green light reaches our eyes.) Tj T*
ET
endstream
